entries.npc_failure_1: Sometimes circumstances get in the way of success. It happens all the time.
entries.npc_noloc_1: Whup! I need to attend to some business that has suddenly arisen. Come back a little later and we'll discuss this project then.
entries.npc_work_1: Have you killed those two dwarf nunas yet? It's hardly a challenge.
entries.npc_reward_1: I see you know how to handle yourself. The next job that comes up is yours.
entries.npc_backtowork_1: So are you going to finish that trial run? It's only a couple of dwarf nunas.
entries.npc_4_1: A simple thing, really -- kill me a pair of dwarf nunas. Not hard by any means, but it'll show me you know how to handle yourself. I'll pay you for your time, of course. What do you say?
entries.npc_3_1: Well, if you won't do this one small thing, I don't imagine you'd be much use on the tougher jobs.
entries.npc_2_1: Good! Come back once you've killed a pair of dwarf nunas, and we'll talk again. Watch out for larger game, though -- there's some mean creatures out there.
entries.npc_1_1: My name's Gerrio Coronis, and I run Theedside Safaris. Are you in need of a few credits? I'm looking for part-time help. I run a safari, you understand, so I need to feel confident you can handle a weapon. Would you do a trial run first? Just to show me you're capable.
entries.npc_reset_1: If you feel like trying again later, I'd certainly welcome you.
entries.cantwork: Just the sort I'm looking for! I'd be happy to hire you, but it seems you already have a job.
entries.next: I don't have any work right now. But maybe if you check back with me later, I can find something for you.
